Here are 13 iced Americanos
and one cafe mocha.

112
00:09:02,850 --> 00:09:03,950
Thank you.

113
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,140
Thank you.

114
00:09:06,490 --> 00:09:07,900
Chungil Prison?

115
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:08,710
Yes.

116
00:09:08,710 --> 00:09:11,770
One of my sources used
to be over there.

117
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:13,790
He was released,
so I saw him yesterday.

118
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:15,200
And?

119
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,580
He knew...

120
00:09:17,940 --> 00:09:19,460
Cha Yo Han very well.

121
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:23,070
6238 who was in Chungil Prison?

122
00:09:23,070 --> 00:09:25,950
I observed that punk carefully.

123
00:09:25,950 --> 00:09:28,040
His physique is quite peculiar.

124
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,560
Very unique.

125
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,390
If this gets out,

126
00:09:31,390 --> 00:09:34,590
no hospital would want Cha Yo Han.

127
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:39,850
What did you hear?

128
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:46,620
Hello.

129
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:47,920
Dr. Cha, we have an emergency.

130
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:48,970
This way!

131
00:09:52,490 --> 00:09:53,340
What the heck?

132
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:54,750
- What's this?
- That way.

133
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,340
One, two, three!

134
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:12,990
- Welcome back!
- Congratulations!

135
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:16,480
Congrats on your return, Dr. Cha.

136
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:19,590
Isn't this too much for someone
who was just disciplined?

137
00:10:19,590 --> 00:10:21,920
No, no. The disciplinary
action was too much.

138
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:25,150
You deserve to be
welcomed back, Dr. Cha!

139
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:27,350
Coffee boy!

140
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:31,200
I brought these.

141
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,110
Wow!

142
00:10:32,110 --> 00:10:34,180
Thank you for the drinks!

143
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:37,470
Dr. Shi Young drew this herself.

144
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,520
It looks just like you!

145
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,160
This is for you, Dr. Shi Young.

146
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,320
Thank you, Dr. Cha.

147
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,350
Ki Seok...

148
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:54,260
Ki Seok, open your eyes.

149
00:11:54,260 --> 00:11:56,320
Ki Seok, Ki Seok, open your eyes.

150
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,470
Ki Seok...

151
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,490
Ki Seok.

152
00:12:10,490 --> 00:12:11,560
- Ki Seok!
- Doctor.

153
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,860
He suddenly collapsed at the gym.

154
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:15,750
He's breathing on his own,
but unconscious.

155
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:16,850
His temperature is 40.5 degrees,

156
00:12:16,850 --> 00:12:18,050
and his pulse is 125.

157
00:12:18,050 --> 00:12:19,090
Blood pressure is 92 over 50.

158
00:12:19,090 --> 00:12:20,100
- Let's move him.
- Ki Seok...

159
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:21,550
- Okay.
- Ki Seok.

160
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,640
One, two, three!

161
00:12:25,010 --> 00:12:28,070
Dr. Cha! My Ki Seok. Please save him.

162
00:12:28,070 --> 00:12:29,590
- Dr. Cha...
- Ma'am.

163
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:31,470
I'll take a look first, okay?

164
00:12:31,470 --> 00:12:32,380
Take her over there.

165
00:12:32,380 --> 00:12:34,040
Please stay calm and step this way.

166
00:12:35,220 --> 00:12:36,300
Ki Seok.

167
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:37,290
Ki Seok?

168
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:38,880
- Sir, are you okay?
- Ki Seok.

169
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,630
He's a CIPA patient.

170
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:43,620
He doesn't respond to pain.

171
00:12:43,620 --> 00:12:45,180
Give me a stethoscope.

172
00:12:59,690 --> 00:13:01,330
He has a bruise on his side.

173
00:13:01,330 --> 00:13:04,600
I'm not sure if it happened
before or as he collapsed.

174
00:13:10,450 --> 00:13:11,810
Ki Seok.

175
00:13:11,810 --> 00:13:13,940
Administer one ampule of Ativan.

176
00:13:13,940 --> 00:13:15,590
Ki Seok.

177
00:13:18,310 --> 00:13:19,480
Ki Seok.

178
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,630
Ki Seok...

179
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:25,130
His brain CT shows no abnormalities.

180
00:13:25,130 --> 00:13:28,190
His temperature won't drop
even with the medication.

181
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:31,710
Couldn't the seizures be
a febrile fit due to the fever?

182
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:33,210
The other lab results?

183
00:13:33,210 --> 00:13:35,030
His CRP is high at 9.2,

184
00:13:35,030 --> 00:13:36,780
and ANC is 615.

185
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:37,980
And the infection focus?

186
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:40,010
I see an infiltration in the right lung.

187
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:41,750
Do you think it's pneumonia?

188
00:13:43,810 --> 00:13:45,170
Administer antibiotics for now.

189
00:13:45,170 --> 00:13:46,820
Such as piperacillin and tazobactam.

190
00:13:46,820 --> 00:13:48,210
Yes, sir.

191
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:59,200
[ Video Analysis Room 1 ]
The part you mentioned...

192
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:02,100
As you can see, we enlarged it
as much as possible, but

193
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:04,110
we can't see anything.

194
00:14:10,290 --> 00:14:13,640
A white gown and short, black hair.

195
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:15,750
A male who's not wearing glasses.

196
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,700
That's about all we know.

197
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:19,200
Yes, correct.

198
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:29,910
- Yes.
- Prosecutor.

199
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:33,930
Do you know that "Famous Healers" is
airing the Cha Yo Han episode tonight?

200
00:14:33,930 --> 00:14:35,390
I'm a little tied up right now.

201
00:14:35,390 --> 00:14:36,590
Let's talk later.

202
00:14:36,590 --> 00:14:37,980
You must watch it!

203
00:14:42,180 --> 00:14:43,510
Please watch it.

204
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,350
I have something to tell you.

205
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,080
We administered antibiotics
and fever reducer.

206
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:54,370
But he's still unconscious with a fever.

207
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:57,080
He's breathing on his own,

208
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,480
but the pneumonia is advancing.

209
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:00,610
We gave him 5ml of Ancef.

210
00:15:00,610 --> 00:15:02,430
Saturation is in the lower 90's.

211
00:15:13,110 --> 00:15:15,610
We may have to get him
on a ventilator soon.

212
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:20,230
Where is Ki Seok's mother?

213
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:25,750
Ma'am.

214
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:28,730
After he was discharged from here,

215
00:15:28,730 --> 00:15:30,630
did he show any unusual symptoms?

216
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,060
No.

217
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:34,590
Then was he injured recently

218
00:15:34,590 --> 00:15:36,640
or go traveling?

219
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:39,830
Nothing out of the ordinary.

220
00:15:39,830 --> 00:15:42,090
He didn't travel, either.

221
00:15:49,980 --> 00:15:52,080
What could it be?

222
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:54,460
Antibiotics and fever
reducers are not working.

223
00:16:05,050 --> 00:16:06,740
Is this Ki Seok's?

224
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:08,590
I think so.

225
00:16:17,770 --> 00:16:18,760
Ma'am.

226
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:21,290
This is Ki Seok's phone, right?
May we take a look?

227
00:16:21,290 --> 00:16:22,250
Sure.

228
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:24,470
Maybe we can get some info.

229
00:16:24,470 --> 00:16:26,010
Like a memo or photographs.

230
00:16:26,010 --> 00:16:28,750
He'd have exchanged texts
with his friends, too.

231
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:30,700
Okay, go ahead and take a look.

232
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:54,100
You said Ki Seok collapsed
at the gym, correct?

233
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:55,090
Yes.

234
00:16:55,090 --> 00:16:56,810
Was Ki Seok into working out?

235
00:16:56,810 --> 00:16:58,580
He didn't before.

236
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:01,850
But he wanted a personal
trainer during his vacation.

237
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:11,110
Ki Seok measured his weight, body fat,
and muscle mass every day.

238
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:12,680
He analyzed himself.

239
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:16,520
At his weight, the body fat and muscle
mass are below average.

240
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:18,580
It couldn't have been to lose weight.

241
00:17:18,580 --> 00:17:20,180
Maybe he was increasing
muscle mass?

242
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:21,430
That's a possibility.

243
00:17:41,650 --> 00:17:43,010
Steroids.

244
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:47,640
Perhaps it's because of steroids?

245
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,720
In order to bulk up their muscles,

246
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:52,740
some people get illegal
steroids shots and work out.

247
00:17:52,740 --> 00:17:54,900
As a side effect, the
immune system collapsed...

248
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:57,120
That steroids is not the same one.

249
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:58,020
Come on now.

250
00:17:58,020 --> 00:17:59,560
Unlike the regular steroids,

251
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:02,170
anabolic steroids which
increase muscle mass

252
00:18:02,170 --> 00:18:03,960
don't repress the immune system.

253
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:07,180
That's right, that's right.
Sorry, I was confused.

254
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:09,480
What if Ki Seok was confused?

255
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:14,040
In his confusion, he injected
the regular steroids?

256
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,490
That's what you're saying, right?

257
00:18:15,490 --> 00:18:16,690
Yes.

258
00:18:31,260 --> 00:18:33,320
Shall we call Ki Seok's mom and

259
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:36,040
ask her to inspect his
gym locker and belongings?

260
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:38,230
We'll go take a look.
Tell her to keep it locked.

261
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:39,420
Yes, sir.

262
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:43,310
The patient we're meeting today...

263
00:18:43,310 --> 00:18:45,620
His body doesn't talk even
though something's wrong.

264
00:18:45,620 --> 00:18:47,290
He's unable to feel pain.

265
00:18:47,290 --> 00:18:51,130
He's suffering from congenital insensitive
to pain with anhidrosis (CIPA).

266
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:53,600
[ CIPA: Congenital insensitive
to pain with anhidrosis. ]

267
00:18:54,270 --> 00:18:58,350
This equipment monitors one's heart
rate to showcase his pain levels.

268
00:18:58,350 --> 00:19:00,430
It's called an ANI machine.

269
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:02,750
When most people feel pain,

270
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,480
their heart rate changes,

271
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:07,120
